  "Description": "The EL357N-G is a 4-pin SMD optocoupler that provides electrical isolation and signal transmission between two circuits. It contains an infrared LED on the input side optically coupled to a phototransistor on the output side. Its primary function is to transfer an electrical signal via light, isolating the input and output sides to prevent ground loops, block high voltages, and allow interfacing between circuits of different potentials.",
